│    {"command":"create","path":"/memories/session/plan.md","file_text":"# Plan: replai Copilot JSONL importer, chooser, CLI flags, tests, docs\n\n## Status of existing code (as of exploration)\n\nAlready implemented in replay_core.py:\n- `_default_workspace_storage_roots()` — cross-platform (macOS/Linux/Win)\n- `_discover_latest_copilot_session()` — globs workspaceStorage for latest main.jsonl by mtime\n- `choose_trajectory_file(root)` — routes explicit session dir / explicit main.jsonl / auto-latest / fallback ATIF scan\n- `load_copilot_jsonl(path)` — streaming importer, user_message/agent_response/tool_call/tool_result/child_session_ref\n- `_parse_agent_response_text()` — extracts only `type=text` parts from response JSON string\n- `_ms_to_iso()`, `_decode_args()`, call/result pairing via spanId\n\nGaps — what needs to be built:\n1. **tool_call parts not extracted from agent_response** — `_parse_agent_response_text` ignores `type=tool_call` parts; the sample fixture already has one; no top-level `tool_call` events in fixture\n2. **`choose_trajectory_file` not wired into `main()`** — `run_serve/run_html/run_play` receive raw `args.file` (None when omitted); auto-discovery never runs\n3. **`--no-latest` flag** — not in replai.py, not in `choose_trajectory_file`\n4. **Tests missing** — tool_call parts, malformed lines, child_session, call/result pairing, --no-latest\n5. **README missing** — no docs at all\n6. **CI smoke script** — nothing in place\n\n---\n\n## Plan: Phase 1 — importer fix (highest priority, unblocks tests)\n\n**Files:** `replay_core.py`\n\n1.1 Rename `_parse_agent_response_text` → `_parse_agent_response_parts(raw) -> tuple[str, list[dict]]` that returns `(text, tool_calls)`. tool_calls are dicts with `{id, name, arguments}`.\n1.2 Update `load_copilot_jsonl` agent_response branch: use `_parse_agent_response_parts`; append extracted tool_calls to `step[\"tool_calls\"]`.\n1.3 Use `spanId` from the outer event as a fallback call_id for parts-extracted tool calls when parts lack an `id`.\n\n## Plan: Phase 2 — wire choose_trajectory_file into CLI\n\n**Files:** `replai.py`, `replay_core.py`\n\n2.1 Add `use_latest: bool = True` param to `choose_trajectory_file`; when False skip `_discover_latest_copilot_session` and go straight to interactive/fallback.\n2.2 In `replai.py`, add `--no-latest` flag to the three subcommands (play/serve/html).\n2.3 In `main()`, before calling `run_*`: if `args.file is None`, call `choose_trajectory_file(\".\", use_latest=not args.no_latest)` and pass the result as `path`. If `args.file` is not None, call `choose_trajectory_file(args.file, use_latest=True)` to normalize (session dir → main.jsonl, file → file).\n2.4 `choose_trajectory_file` should return `Optional[Path]` and return None / exit when no_latest + no files (instead of always sys.exit). `main()` handles None.\n\n## Plan: Phase 3 — tests & fixtures\n\n**Files:** `tests/test_copilot_importer.py`, new fixture files\n\n3.1 Add `tests/fixtures/copilot_debug_logs/full_session/main.jsonl` — richer fixture with:\n  - user_message\n  - agent_response (with type=text + type=tool_call parts)\n  - tool_result (referencing call_1)\n  - another user_message\n  - agent_response (text only)\n  - child_session_ref pointing to `child.jsonl`\n3.2 Add `tests/fixtures/copilot_debug_logs/full_session/child.jsonl` — minimal fixture with one agent_response.\n3.3 New tests in `test_copilot_importer.py`:\n  - `test_tool_calls_extracted_from_agent_response_parts` — asserts tool_calls on agent step\n  - `test_tool_result_paired_to_call` — asserts observation.results[0].source_call_id == call_id\n  - `test_child_session_flattened` — asserts child step appears in doc[\"steps\"]\n  - `test_malformed_lines_skipped` — create jsonl with bad lines mixed with good; assert no exception, correct steps count\n  - `test_no_latest_skips_auto_discovery` — monkeypatches `_discover_latest_copilot_session` to fail, passes no_latest=True, asserts no auto-pick\n  - `test_choose_file_normalizes_non_main_jsonl_path` — passes explicit .jsonl file (not named main.jsonl), asserts returned path == input\n3.4 Existing tests should still pass (no regression).\n\n## Plan: Phase 4 — README & CI smoke\n\n**Files:** `README.md` (create), `Makefile` or `scripts/smoke.sh` (create)\n\n4.1 Create `README.md` covering: purpose, install (`pip install -r requirements.txt`), three CLI commands with examples, `--no-latest` flag, how to smoke test.\n4.2 Add smoke test note at bottom of README and a `make smoke` target or `scripts/smoke.sh` that runs `python -m pytest -q` and `python replai.py html tests/fixtures/copilot_debug_logs/full_session --output /tmp/replai-smoke.html`.\n\n---\n\n## Relevant files\n\n- `replay_core.py` — `_parse_agent_response_text`, `load_copilot_jsonl`, `choose_trajectory_file`, `_discover_latest_copilot_session`\n- `replai.py` — `_build_parser`, `main` — CLI wiring\n- `browser_view.py` — `_load_doc_and_events`, `run_serve`, `run_html` — no changes needed ([truncated] │
│  )                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     │
